cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR

The paper proposes a new approach for computer-aided diagnosis using convolutional neural networks (CNN) and Gray-Level Co-Occurrence Matrix (GLCM) for medical image classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of image segmentation, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
